events.name: TCU Horned Frogs at New Mexico Lobos

headlines.description: Andy Dalton threw three touchdown passes before leaving with an elbow injury and No. 4 TCU capped its second straight undefeated season with a second consecutive Mountain West championship, beating lowly New Mexico 66-17 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: TCU clinches another perfect year

events.name: LSU Tigers at Arkansas Razorbacks

headlines.description: Ryan Mallett threw for 320 yards and three touchdowns as No. 12 Arkansas made its case for the school's first BCS bowl game with a 31-23 win over No. 6 LSU on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Arkansas states BCS case

events.name: Oregon State Beavers at Stanford Cardinal

headlines.description: Andrew Luck threw four touchdown passes to set a single-season school record and No. 7 Stanford stated its case for a berth in the Bowl Championship Series by beating Oregon State 38-0 Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stanford states BCS case

events.name: Northwestern Wildcats at Wisconsin Badgers

headlines.description: No. 5 Wisconsin has earned a share of the Big Ten championship with its 70-23 rout of Northwestern on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dominant Wisconsin joins knot atop Big Ten

events.name: Michigan Wolverines at Ohio State Buckeyes

headlines.description: No. 8 Ohio State's defense stymied high-powered Michigan 37-7 on Saturday, stretching the Buckeyes' mastery in "The Game" to seven straight wins.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ohio State stymies archrival Michigan

events.name: Oklahoma Sooners at Oklahoma State Cowboys

headlines.description: Miami fired coach Randy Shannon on Saturday night, hours after the Hurricanes finished a 7-5 regular season that began with championship expectations.
headlines.shortLinkText: OU clips Okla. St. for 3-way Big 12 tie

events.name: Michigan State Spartans at Penn State Nittany Lions

headlines.description: No. 11 Michigan State has claimed at least a share of its first Big Ten title since 1990 after beating Penn State 28-22 at blustery Beaver Stadium.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spartans snag share of Big Ten

events.name: Kansas Jayhawks at Missouri Tigers

headlines.description: Blaine Gabbert directed scoring drives on No. 15 Missouri's first two possessions and later scored on a 1-yard run himself, leading the Tigers to a 35-7 victory over Kansas on Saturday
headlines.shortLinkText: Missouri holds Kansas to 141 yards in victory

events.name: Virginia Cavaliers at Virginia Tech Hokies

headlines.description: Ryan Williams ran for two touchdowns and No. 13 Virginia Tech won its 10th consecutive game and seventh in a row over Virginia, 37-7, on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Va. Tech vaults Virginia for 10th win in a row

events.name: South Carolina Gamecocks at Clemson Tigers

headlines.description: Stephen Garcia threw for two touchdowns, Alshon Jeffery had his seventh 100-yard receiving game and No. 18 South Carolina posted its third nine-win season ever with a 29-7 victory over rival Clemson on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: S. Carolina handles Clemson in SEC title tuneup

events.name: BYU Cougars at Utah Utes

headlines.description: Brandon Burton blocked a last-second field goal to lift No. 23 Utah to a wild 17-16 victory Saturday over BYU in their final game as Mountain West Conference rivals.
headlines.shortLinkText: Last-second FG block helps Utah shake off BYU

events.name: Florida Gators at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: Christian Ponder threw for 221 yards and three touchdowns Saturday to lead No. 22 Florida State to a 31-7 win over Florida that snapped a six-game losing streak in the series by the Seminoles.
headlines.shortLinkText: FSU clubs Gators for title shot

events.name: NC State Wolfpack at Maryland Terrapins

headlines.description: Danny O'Brien threw for a career-high 417 yards and four touchdowns, all to Torrey Smith, and Maryland denied No. 21 North Carolina State a spot in the Atlantic Coast Conference title game by defeating the Wolfpack 38-31 Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: O'Brien throws 4 TDs as Terps storm NC State

events.name: Iowa Hawkeyes at Minnesota Golden Gophers

headlines.description: Duane Bennett's touchdown run with 4:31 left lifted Minnesota to 27-24 victory Saturday over 24th-ranked Iowa, as the Hawkeyes lost another fourth-quarter lead and fell to the rival Gophers for the first time in four years.
headlines.shortLinkText: Iowa undone: Minnesota knocks off Hawkeyes

events.name: Mississippi State Bulldogs at Ole Miss Rebels

headlines.description: Chris Relf threw for a career-high 288 yards and three touchdowns as No. 25 Mississippi State beat Mississippi 31-23 on Saturday night in the Egg Bowl.
headlines.shortLinkText: Miss. State halts Ole Miss rally to win Egg Bowl

events.name: Cincinnati Bearcats at Connecticut Huskies

headlines.description: EAST HARTFORD, Conn. -- Connecticut's Jordan Todman ran for 175 yards and three touchdowns and the Huskies moved a step closer to a BCS bowl berth Saturday with a 38-17 win over Cincinnati.
headlines.shortLinkText: UConn handles Cincy to remain in Big East mix

events.name: Boston College Eagles at Syracuse Orange

headlines.description: Freshman tailback Andre Williams rushed for 185 yards on a school-record 42 carries and scored one touchdown in place of injured star Montel Harris, Nate Freese kicked three field goals, and Boston College beat Syracuse 16-7 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williams fills Harris' shoes as BC beats Cuse

headlines.description: UCF 37, Memphis 17
headlines.shortLinkText: UCF 37, Memphis 17

headlines.description: Marshall 38, Tulane 23
headlines.shortLinkText: Marshall 38, Tulane 23

events.name: South Florida Bulls at Miami Hurricanes

headlines.description: MIAMI -- Demetris Murray had a 1-yard touchdown run in overtime and South Florida stunned Miami 23-20 on Saturday, sending the Hurricanes to their worst season at home since 1997.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray, South Florida upend Miami in overtime

events.name: Indiana Hoosiers at Purdue Boilermakers

headlines.description: Indiana's Mitch Ewald booted a 26-yard field goal with 9 seconds left to force overtime Saturday, then won it with a 31-yarder to give Indiana a 34-31 victory over Purdue to win the Old Oaken Bucket.
headlines.shortLinkText: Indiana halts 12-game Big Ten skid with OT win

events.name: Kentucky Wildcats at Tennessee Volunteers

headlines.description: KNOXVILLE, Tenn. -- Tyler Bray threw for 354 yards and two touchdowns as Tennessee extended its winning streak over Kentucky to 26 straight games to become bowl eligible with a 24-14 victory on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bray helps Vols overcome Kentucky in 2nd half

events.name: Washington Huskies at California Golden Bears

headlines.description: Chris Polk scored on a 1-yard run as time expired, and Washington denied California bowl eligibility while keeping its own postseason hopes alive with a thrilling 16-13 victory Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Washington denies Cal shot at bowl with late TD

events.name: North Carolina Tar Heels at Duke Blue Devils

headlines.description: T.J. Yates threw for 264 yards and a touchdown, and North Carolina continued its dominance of Duke by holding off the Blue Devils 24-19 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: UNC holds off pesky Duke to close out season

events.name: Kansas State Wildcats at North Texas Mean Green

headlines.description: Daniel Thomas rushed for a career-high 269 yards and Kansas State closed the college home of "Mean" Joe Greene by rallying for a 49-41 victory against North Texas on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: N. Texas falls to Kansas St. in Fouts Field finale

events.name: Wake Forest Demon Deacons at Vanderbilt Commodores

headlines.description: Josh Harris rushed for 138 yards and one touchdown and Wake Forest defeated Vanderbilt 34-13 on Saturday night in Robbie Caldwell's last game as Vanderbilt's head coach.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harris, Wake Forest ruin Caldwell's Vandy finale

events.name: Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets at Georgia Bulldogs

headlines.description: Aaron Murray threw for three touchdowns, Justin Houston returned a fumble 18 yards for a score and Georgia Tech missed a tying extra point, giving Georgia the win it needed to be eligible for a bowl, a 42-34 victory over the Yellow Jackets on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Georgia edges Georgia Tech for bowl eligibility

events.name: Notre Dame Fighting Irish at USC Trojans

headlines.description: Notre Dame rallied to snap an eight-game losing streak in college football's best intersectional rivalry with a 20-16 victory over Southern California.
headlines.shortLinkText: Irish grab first win over USC since '01

events.name: Houston Cougars at Texas Tech Red Raiders

headlines.description: Taylor Potts threw for 373 yards and four touchdowns to lead Texas Tech over Houston 35-20 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Potts help Texas Tech gain revenge on Houston
